tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient"s HbA1c is mildly elevated, indicating impaired glucose regulation or possible prediabetes, while fasting glucose is within normal limits. Renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are all within normal ranges. No acute abnormalities detected aside from the elevated HbA1c; recommend follow-up for glycemic control and diabetes risk assessment.
